<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>qhor</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>...and don't look back.<br />
<br />
i bought my horse yesterday, and the difference is huge.<br />
somebody suggested it's around FT 20 - perhaps not that extreme, but a horse gives me a regen boost almost akin to KEI when i'm soloing.<br />
<br />
how the horse changed my solo strategy:<br />
<br />
i never used to tank for my pet - w/o a horse, HP is simply too precious to waste tanking.  decreased HP regen rate = decreased mana regen rate = decreased kill rate.  so i'd pull, tank until pet taunted once, e-bolt and back off, sit, root if need be.<br />
<br />
now, however, i tank for my pet (letting it have the mob's back - no dodges/parries) and still regen sitting mana, making the sacrificed HP less crucial.  no need to regen or defensively buff pet, and i can work up weapon skills and add a little of my own meager DPS. i find my kill rate increased dramatically, maybe around 25%.<br />
<br />
grouping:<br />
<br />
well, the big issue is aggro management since i'm usually not OOM in groups unless i have to rebuff.  but needless to say, horsey helps a lot with aggro (no sitting).<br />
<br />
downsides:<br />
<br />
the head gets in the way, yeah. shrink x2 and it's pretty much gone.<br />
the old bug with turning off horses/your luclin graphic doesn't work anymore ('You must enable both your race graphic and horse graphic to summon a mount.'), so you still need to deal with the acceleration and decreased run speed (compared to SoW).  no big deal, though - bih'li and horse stack, so if you get in a pinch just click off mount and run for it.<br />
you only receive sitting mana regen while on a horse; HP regens as though you were standing.  this might in theory  be a problem if a larger portion of a shaman's regen came from sitting vs standing.  however, as a barbarian with regen III and regrowth up, i regen 20 HP standing vs. 23 sitting.  again, NBD.<br />
<br />
so that's about it... i did a lot of research and asked a lot of questions before buying my mount, but in retrospect i should've bought first and worried later.  it's hands down the gear upgrade that's yielded the most significant improvement in gameplay i've bought. (no JBB yet though)<br />
<br />
anyway, just thought i'd post in case any of you are considering buying a horse.  do it <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=629488<br />
">teiresias</a> of lanys.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
